# MuseDAM Figma Layer/Component Naming Rules

## Trigger Conditions
- Figma link provided (https://www.figma.com/file/... or https://figma.com/design/...)
- Mention of “Figma file”, “design in Figma”, “restore from Figma”

## Forced Execution Flow
1. Extract File Key from link.
2. Naming priority:
   - Component/Instance → use ComponentNode.name (with variant: Button/Primary/Medium)
   - Frame/Section → use as page/block name (e.g. IPLibraryPage, HeaderSection)
   - Group/Auto Layout → semantic name or parent+child combination
   - Atomic layers → only for internal className/data-testid
3. Naming convention:
   - PascalCase: AssetCard, ConfirmDialog
   - Variants with / : Button/Primary/Large
   - Path: src/components/ui/ or domain folder
4. In code:
   - File/export name = extracted semantic name
   - Add data-component="original Figma name"
   - If layers are generic (Frame 1, Group 45), warn user to rename in Figma.

## Mapping Example (from your project)
- approval-center/ → ApprovalCenterPage
- AssetThumbnail.tsx → AssetThumbnail
- icons/ → SearchIcon, SettingsIcon, etc.